2akN:@wQl=;MsX}i/D)e.text: Remove the "Example attack" block, then you can add your custom attack to this block. Explanation on how to use the custom attack blocks are below

`+f%_]Ul(yQX/wjI@Ny%.text: This will create a bone. They come from size 1-27, with the highest the soul can jump over from the ground being 13. You can set their speed also. There are 4 types of bones possible: REGULAR RIGHT or  REGULAR LEFT will fire a regular bone from either the right or left. BLUE RIGHT or BLUE LEFT will do the same thing but with a blue bone, and ORANGE RIGHT or ORANGE LEFT with an orange bone. Note that entering a type other than REGULAR RIGHT, REGULAR LEFT, BLUE RIGHT, BLUE LEFT, ORANGE RIGHT, or ORANGE LEFT will not work.

p?rG/-!]dM2!#s%G`O}*.text: This will create a platform that will come from the left or right of the screen that the soul can jump on. The platforms only work with DOWN gravity. Having the Y position of 0 will cause the platform to be in the middle of the box, but you can make it come from higher or lower. You can set its speed (the speed of the SOUL is 4) and set its size, from 1-20.

VgKVMq(ZTVMjkqt^Dx`|.text: This will cause the screen to blink, deleting all of the bones and platforms and causing the soul to reset at either the left, middle, or right of the box. You can also set the box size to small, medium, or large.
